Cell.Text: I have an important message from General Tullius.
[E] No doubt requesting to garrison his men in my castle. How many times must I deny him? | Well? Out with it.
About that message from the General...
G|We can talk about that once this dragon is dealt with.
About that message from the General...
[S] G|Ah yes. I've studied those documents... Very interesting...
Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak asked me to deliver this axe to you.
Did he now? The man is persistent, I'll give him that.
About that message from Ulfric...
G|We can talk about that once this dragon is dealt with.
About that message from the Jarl...
[S] G|Ah yes. | I suppose it's time I gave him an answer...

Node.Caption: CW03BalgruufTopic: I have an important message for you.

Cell.Text: Until that dragon's dealt with, I don't care what Tullius wants. | For now, give the papers to my Steward.
I see... Give the papers to my Steward.
But until that dragon's dealt with, Ulfric's just going to have to wait. | For now, I'll hold onto this axe. But it's a tenuous peace at best.
[S] G|I suppose it's time I give him an answer...

Node.Caption: CW03BalgruufReason: Ulfric plans to attack Whiterun. The General wants to lend Legion troops.

Cell.Text: [S] Don't be daft. Proventus is my eyes. | Just give me the letter. I presume once I have it, I can do as I please with it? Good.

Node.Caption: CW03BalgruufJarlsEyesOnly: I was given strict instructions. For the Jarl's eyes only.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Now, I believe you have some business to conclude with my court wizard?
[S] G|Now get out of here and to the outpost! I need to know what's happening out there.
[S] G|Hmm... these are interesting reports...
G|One moment. But don't go far. I expect I'll need you.
S|I've made up my mind, even if my advisors are still squabbling. I'm sending you to Windhelm.
[S] Deliver this axe to Ulfric Stormcloak.
[S] G|[E] You can return this axe to our friend. The esteemed Jarl of Windhelm has my answer. Make sure he gets it.

Node.Caption: CW03BalgruufAxeTopic: You have a task for me?

Cell.Text: How long have you been in Skyrim? Yes. Give the man my axe. | If he returns it to you it means we have business to settle. If he keeps it, then we are at peace.
[E] Men who understand one another need not waste words. | There are but a few simple truths behind one warrior giving another his axe. | Ulfric will know my meaning.

Node.Caption: CW03BalgruufAxeSayAnything: Should I say anything to him?

Cell.Text: G|Good. | Good...
Is that so? I've been wondering when he'd come around.
The Jarl of Whiterun returns your axe.
[S] G|Then I was wrong about him.

Node.Caption: CW03UlfricReturnAxeTopic: I've brought a message from the Jarl of Whiterun.

Cell.Text: [S] Oh. What's this? | Ahhh... You're quite brave to carry such a message. It's a pity you've chosen the wrong side... | [E] You can return this axe to the man who sent it. And tell him he should prepare to entertain... visitors. | [E] I expect a great deal of excitement in the city of Whiterun in the near future...
G|Sooner than you think.

I have shown the people that when our Jarls drink the Empire's milk, it makes us weak. | I must now show them the path that will lead us back to our strength. | There is no progress without sacrifice. No wheat without threshing the chaff. | The Empire and the Jarls who back them must be swept away. The people demand it. I demand it.

Node.Caption: CW03UlfricReturnAxeWhy: You've killed the High King. Why make war on your own people?

Cell.Text: Oh? True, I may meet my end in a dark ally with a dagger in my back. But the people have seen the truth, and they will not back down.

[S] You've returned with my axe. I knew that would be his response. | As soon as you left I sent word to General Tullius, who's been kind enough to lend us some of his troops and Legate Cipius here. | Let Ulfric try to make it past our combined forces. | I'll turn you back over to your Legion. Legate Cipius will have use for you. Gods be with us all.
Make haste to our camp in Whiterun. I want you on the front lines. | [E] I have a feeling about you. Your place is on that battlefield. I need you there.
[S] G|Fight well, or die well. Talos be with you!
[S] G|Then I commit them to whatever gods they still believe in. | Talos be with you!

Node.Caption: CW03UlfricGreetWarManyWillDie: Many will die by my hand.

Cell.Text: True, he's a dangerous and blood thirsty man, but he's also a Nord that honors our traditions. | Keep your wits about you and you won't be harmed. | And then get back here. Because if Ulfric isn't bluffing, I'll need every able body to defend Whiterun.

Node.Caption: CW03BalgruufAxeDangerous: And you think Ulfric will let me just walk in there, no trouble?
